<HEADLINE> Armenia Beats Albania 3-0 in European World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Armenia outplayed Albania 3-0
in their World Cup European Group nine qualifier on Saturday in
Yerevan, Armenia.
</P>
<P>
The two teams played to a 0-0 tie in the first half.
</P>
<P>
The home team opened the scorings through Kharutyun Vardanyan
in the 60th minute.
</P>
<P>
Eric Assaturyan added the second in the 82nd minute while
Garnik Avalyan rounded off the victory for Armenia by a penalty
with just two minutes to go before the final whistle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
