<HEADLINE> Ireland Beats Iceland 4-2 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Ireland outplayed Iceland
4-2 in their World Cup European Group 8 qualifier on Saturday in
Reykjavik, capital of Iceland.
</P>
<P>
The two squads played to a 1-1 tie in the first half.
</P>
<P>
David Connolly opened the scorings in the 13th minute for the
visiting team while Brynjar Bjorn Gunnarsson pulled back 1-1 in
the 44th minute.
</P>
<P>
Just at the beginning of the second half, Helgi Sigurdsson put
Iceland ahead. However, the home fans joy didn't last long as Roy
Keane of Ireland found net twice in the 53rd and 65th minute
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Mark Kennedy wrapped up the victory for Ireland with a goal in
the 79th minute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
