<HEADLINE> Road Accident Kills 36 People in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 6 (Xinhua) -- One of the worst road
accidents happened in Ethiopia during the weekend, killing 36
people, the Southern African Broadcasting Association reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Radio Ethiopia was quoted as saying that a bus, with 50 people
on board, plunged into a ravine 130 metre deep, killing the 36
people instantly.
</P>
<P>
Only one woman managed to escape with minor injuries and 13
others were seriously injured.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred 11 kilometres north of Dessie Town,
about 400 kilometres north of Addis Ababa, the Ethiopian capital.
</P>
<P>
The crash is the worst traffic accident in the country this
year, the radio said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
