<HEADLINE> Tobacco Promotion in Africa Must be Stopped: WHO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 6 (Xinhua) -- A top official of the
World Health Organisation (WHO) said today that unregulated
promotion of tobacco products in Africa is immoral and must be
stopped.
</P>
<P>
Ebrahim Samba, WHO's African regional director made the call
at the on-going meeting of African health ministers held in Sun
City, 200 kilometres north-west of Pretoria, local press
reported.
</P>
<P>
Tobacco companies are turning to Africa as they are losing out
in other regions such as America and Europe because of a strong
campaign waged against smoking, he said.
</P>
<P>
Young people in Africa are being targeted aggressively by
these tobacco firms, Samba added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
