<BODY>
<HEADLINE> King Hussein to Attend Tripartite Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, September 6 (Xinhua) -- King Hussein of Jordan will
attend a tripartite summit Sunday in Cairo with Egyptian President
Hosni Mubarak and Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat, a senior
official said here today.
</P>
<P>
The summit would deal with the "very serious consequences" and
review latest developments in the Middle East after three bombings
blasted Thursday in West Jerusalem, Jordanian Minister of State
for Information Affairs Samir Mutawe said at a cabinet session.
</P>
<P>
The summit comes "as a part of the continuing process of
coordination and consultation among the leaders of the three
countries," he said.
</P>
<P>
The explosions Thursday that killed seven people and wounded
192 others, together with the double suicide bombings on July 30
which claimed 16 lives, have overshadowed U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright's first visit to the region scheduled for
Tuesday, which is aimed at reviving the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Jordan and Egypt are major players in pushing forward the
Palestinian-Israeli peace talks that have been stalled since
Israel broke ground to build settlements in Arab East Jerusalem in
March this year.
</P>
<P>
They are now the only countries in the Arab world that have
signed peace treaties and established diplomatic relations with
Israel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
