<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada's Banks Reap Huge Profits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Canada's six largest banks
raked in huge profits in the third quarter of their fiscal year,
generating another round of double-digit profit increases.
</P>
<P>
Their total net earnings hit 1.97 billion Canadian dollars
(1.41 billion US dollars) in the three-month period ended July 31,
said reports today.
</P>
<P>
This figure is 15 percent higher than in the second quarter and
24 percent higher than in the same quarter of last year.
</P>
<P>
In the year to date, Canada's Big Six banks have earned 5.4
billion dollars (3.8 billion US dollars), putting them within easy
distance of surpassing the 6.26 billion dollar (4.5 billion US
dollar) profit they earned in fiscal 1996.
</P>
<P>
The Bank of Nova Scotia, the country's fourth largest bank,
recorded the most spectacular showing in the third quarter. Its
profit was 40 percent higher than in the same quarter last year.
</P>
<P>
The only bank to show a drop in earnings was the sixth largest
National Bank of Canada.
</P>
<P>
But its 11-percent fall was a result of artificially high
profits in last year's third quarter, when it sold off a foreign
investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
