<HEADLINE> Mozambique to Rehabilitate Port Maputo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 6 (Xinhua) -- The container terminal
at Maputo Port in the Mozambican capital is to undergo a major
face-lift this year, a report reaching here from Maputo said.
</P>
<P>
The rehabilitation project, to cost eight million U.S.
Dollars, involves the repair of two container handling cranes and
other equipments, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The project will restore the terminal's handling capacity to
more than 100,000 tons per year, according to a government
statement issued in Maputo.
</P>
<P>
The Commonwealth Development Corporation, a British lending
institution, has agreed to provide a loan for the project.
Mozambique joined the commonwealth in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
