<HEADLINE> Vilnius International Conference Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VILNIUS, September 6 (Xinhua) -- The international conference
of Coexistence of Nations and Good Neighborly Relations -- the
Guarantee of Security and Stability in Europe wound up here today
without any result.
</P>
<P>
At today's session, 17 representatives and scientists from
various Central and East European countries and organizations
spoke on the issues of reconciliation of states after World War
II, coexistence of nations and their cooperation.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that peaceful coexistence of nations and equal
cooperation -- the guarantee of security and stability in Europe,
which had experienced too much flames of war in the several
hundred years past.
</P>
<P>
European nations, which do not want to go back to the period of
confrontation, are fighting against military and economic
domination and hope to coordinate and develop their economy in
accordance with the principles of equality and mutual benefit, the
representatives said in their speeches.
</P>
<P>
The international conference, which opened Friday, was
initiated by Lithuanian President Algirdas Brazauskas and his
Polish counterpart, Alexander Kwasniewski, and was attended by
the presidents of Belarus, Estonia, Latvia, Ukraine, Bulgaria,
Hungary, Finland, Moldavia and Romania and Russian Prime Minister
Viktor Chernomyrdin.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador in Lithuania Wang Zhaoxian was also invited
to attend the conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
