<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Industrialists Urged to Unite for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian idustrialists
have been urged to team up to push for industrial changes and
development in the country.
</P>
<P>
The appeal was made here today by Juma Mwapachu, Chairman of
the Confederation of Tanzanian Industrialists (CTI), when he
addressed a one-day meeting to review the government 1997/98
budget.
</P>
<P>
Mwapachu called on industrialists to join the CTI, saying,
"This is the moment we must come together, all of us, in the
Tanzanian business community, to galvanize our resources,
information, experience, judgement and collective wisdom to forge
a forceful and creative mental stew."
</P>
<P>
He said that there is much to be done to enhance the business
environment in the country and make it more competitive and
attractive to investors and other economic players.
</P>
<P>
On the same occation, businessman Ali Mufuruki, who is the
Executive Director of Infotech Computers, called on local
businessmen to be aggressive through tapping markets in
neighboring countries, such as the Democratic Republic of Congo,
which is a ready market for various goods from Tanzania. 
</P>
