<HEADLINE> Lebanon Exults over Defeating Israeli Commando </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Lebanon was immersed today in
the celebrations for the victory made by Lebanese army and
resistance fighters in the fighting against Israeli troops in
south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The Lebanese official National News Agency reported that
Lebanese Defense Minister Emile Lahoud has sent a message of
congratulation to the soldiers who took part in Friday's battles
with Israeli troops, praising their efforts and sacrifice in
order to preserve national honor and protect its people.
</P>
<P>
Early morning on Friday, Lebanese army and resistance
fighters of Iranian-backed Hezbullah and the Shiite Movement
Amal successfully ambushed an Israeli commando who attempted to
attack an Amal base in a village about 45 kilometers north of the
Israeli border, leaving 11 Israeli soldiers dead, four wounded
and one missing.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese former prime minister Salim Hoss said that the
victory under the cooperation among Lebanese army, resistance
fighters and Lebanese people opened a new chapter in resisting
Israeli aggression and gave them a costly lesson.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Lebanese House Speaker Nabih Berri, also
leader of the Shiite Movement Amal who was the major participant
in the battle, received several messages of congratulation from
other Lebanese parties.
</P>
<P>
In addition, almost all Lebanese newspapers carried extensive
coverage of the battle and praised Lebanese fighters as heroes.
</P>
<P>
"The heroism of the army and the resistance inflicted a big
defeat on the Israelis," the opposition daily Ad Diyar said.
</P>
<P>
The banner line of daily An Nahar described the Israeli
defeat as the biggest in Lebanon since the 1982 invasion.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
