<HEADLINE> China's Computer Market on High Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- China's computer market
registered a 39.1 percent growth during the first half of this
year, making the country the fastest emerging consumer of personal
computers in the world.
</P>
<P>
China claimed 23 percent of the PC sales of the Asia-Pacific
region, with the exception of Japan, in the January-June period
this year, representing the largest buying force in the region,
according to a survey report from Dataquest, an
internationally-renowned market survey firm based in the United
States.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Legend Group, the biggest PC seller in China, ranked
eighth among the region's top 10 PC makers, and held a market
share of 2.45 percent.
</P>
<P>
Attracted by the high growth and profitability of the market,
more and more newcomers, mainly from the domestic industrial
sector, jumped on the bandwagon in spite of the increasingly stiff
competition among Chinese and foreign brands.
</P>
<P>
Heguang Group, one of the leading computer agents in China,
launched its own PC brand at the end of August in Beijing,
Shanghai and three other Chinese cities, and opened more than 30
specialty shops and seven maintenance centers across the country.
</P>
<P>
Xu Lingyu, vice-president of Heguang, said that the group has
formed a production capacity of 200,000 PCs annually in addition
to having one of the strongest sales networks in the country, and
thus is prepared to draw lines in the sand with any PC giant.
</P>
<P>
Before this, the market began a new round of competition with
the participation of several big-sized electronics firms,
including Hisense, one of the country's largest household
electronic appliance manufacturers, and Shida Group in Fujian.
</P>
<P>
Joel Stead, vice-president of Seagate, the world's largest
supplier of hard discs, said that about three million PCs will be
sold on the Chinese mainland this year, and thus providing a great
business opportunity for most computer makers here.
</P>
<P>
The company spent 25 million US dollars on its producing base
in Wuxi, Jiangsu Province, last year, and the Seagate investment
will reach 200 million dollars in the Chinese market this year, he
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
