<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Building Materials Industry Witnesses Rapid Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- China's building materials
industry has witnessed an annual growth rate of 25.2 percent in
output value over the last five years.
</P>
<P>
With a large number of infrastructural and housing projects
underway, the industry has entered its best development period
yet, officials say, adding that the industry accomplished its
tasks outlined in the Eighth Five-Year Plan (1991-95) ahead of
schedule.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the output of cement reached 490 million
tons last year, accounting for more than a third of the world
total. Output of plate glass came to 160 million boxes, accounting
for nearly 30 percent of the world total.
</P>
<P>
The production of glass has registered a rapid increase and has
basically met the demand by the country's building and automobile
industries, officials say.
</P>
<P>
The industry's overall output value reached 435.2 billion
yuan (54.4 billion US dollars) in 1996 and its sales
income came to 396.9 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The state has adjusted the structure of the cement and glass
sectors, encouraging the launching of large projects and the
production of quality products.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the production proportion of large and
medium-sized factories is on the rise, as is the ratio of
high-grade products such as toughened glass.
</P>
<P>
A nationwide survey of industrial products shows that
first-class products of the building materials industry account
for more than 70 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
Another survey showed that 86.4 percent of the building
materials meet the state standards set in 1996, 9.2 percentage
points higher than the country's average level.
</P>
<P>
In addition, more products in the industry have adopted
international standards, with the ratio climbing to 41 percent
from 15 percent in 1985. Early this year, 113 million tons of
cement were reported to be up to international standards.
</P>
<P>
Over the past decade, some 11.7 billion dollars worth of
building materials have been exported, with an annual growth rate
of 23 percent.
</P>
<P>
Last year witnessed the exportation of 2.17 billion
dollars of building materials, 6.4-fold higher than in 1987.
</P>
<P>
More end products have been exported, with the ratio rising to
70 percent last year, the survey shows.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
