<HEADLINE> Beijing Aims to Be World's High, New Technology Hub </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Beijing aims to build its
experimental zone of new technology industrial development into an
international hub of high and new technology in three to five
years.
</P>
<P>
The zone is the first national high and new technology
development zone in the Chinese capital city. Centered around
Zhongguancun district in the northwest part of the city, the zone
has a total area of 100 sq km.
</P>
<P>
Efforts to step up its development will be focused on
transformation of the present growth mode, innovation of
technology, enlargement of the industrial scope, and expansion of
overseas market.
</P>
<P>
Currently, there are 4,506 new technology businesses in the
zone, including some of China's leading computer and information
companies like Legend, Stone and Founder.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the zone turned out an industrial output value of 13
billion yuan, and an export volume of 267 million US dollars. The
targets for the year 2000 are: 35 billion yuan in industrial
output value, one billion US dollars in export volume, and two
billion yuan in taxes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
