<HEADLINE> China's Success Provides Example for Others, Cuban Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- China has made amazing
achievements since its adopting the opening-up and reform policy
and the forthcoming 15th congress of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) is important to the country's future, a high-ranking Cuban
official said.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Lage Davila, vice chairman of the Council of State and
executive secretary of the Council of Ministers, said in an
interview with Xinhua, " Great changes have taken place in China
in recent 20 years. Its economy has obtained a rapid development
and the people's living standards have been greatly improved."
</P>
<P>
"I witnessed the changes during my two visits to China in 1992
and 1993," he said.
</P>
<P>
Lage said that the great success of China should be attributed
to the CPC's correct leadership and the opening-up and reform
policy.
</P>
<P>
China's economy has been growing at an average annual rate
of 9 percent, as a result, China realized the target of doubling
its gross national product (GNP) five years ahead of schedule,
Lage said.
</P>
<P>
The grain output of China has reached 500 million tons and its
steel production has gone up to 100 million tons, he added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, China has successfully curbed inflation, he noted.
</P>
<P>
It is remarkable that China is able to feed a huge population
which accounts for 22 percent of the world's total while it is
blessed with only seven percent of the world's arable land, he
said.
</P>
<P>
China adopted its development course according to its own
national conditions and did not blindly follow others, he said.
</P>
<P>
This, as part of China's experiences in economic development,
is what other nations could draw on, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Cuba also values late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping's wise
theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics and will
learn what is suitable for Cuba," Lage said.
</P>
<P>
He spoke highly of the CPC's forthcoming congress, which he
said would further consolidate China's political system and lead
to an economically stronger China.
</P>
<P>
China will make greater contribution to peace and stability in
the world, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
