<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Coulthard Wins Italian Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Britain's David Coulthard won the
Italian Grand Prix in Monza on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Coulthard, driving a McLaren, clocked one hours 17 minutes and
4.609 seconds for the win, 1.937 seconds ahead of second placer
Frenchman Jean Alesi in a Benetton.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Heinz-Harald Frenzen in a Williams finished third
with 4.343 seconds behind.
</P>
<P>
Michael Schumacher retains the lead in the driver's world
championship race, ten points ahead of his nearest rival Jacques
Villeneuve, with four grand prix left. 
</P>
</TEXT>
