<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japan Beats Uzbekistan in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Kazuyoshi Miura scored four
goals to lead Japan to a 6-3 win over Uzbekistan here on Sunday in
their opening match of Asia's World Cup final qualifying round.
</P>
<P>
The win gave Japan the early lead in Group B, which also
includes South Korea, Kazakhstan and the United Arab Emirates.
</P>
<P>
Miura put the home side ahead in the fifth minute when he
converted a penalty after defender Masami Ihara was tripped in the
box. He doubled the lead in the 24th minute.
</P>
<P>
Hidetoshi Nakata and Shoji Jo also scored to give Japan a 4-0
halftime lead.
</P>
<P>
Uzbekistan finally found the net with a 57th-minute goal from
Igor Shkvyrin.
</P>
<P>
But Miura completed his hat-trick 11 minutes later to keep
Japan well ahead.
</P>
<P>
Uzbekistan drew to 5-3 with a penalty by Andrey Fyodorov in the
70th minute and another goal by Oleg Shatskikh six minutes later.
</P>
<P>
In the dying minutes Miura wrapped up the match with his 54th
goal in 78 international matches.  
</P>
</TEXT>
