<HEADLINE> India Beats Bangladesh 3-0 in SA Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 7 (Xinhua) -- India trounced Bangladesh
3-0 here on Sunday afternoon at the first South Asian Football
Federation (SAFF) Championship.
</P>
<P>
After a goalless first half, India's I.M. Vijayan took the lead
30 minutes into the second half. The ball rebound out of the goal
area after hitting the inner side of the crossbeam but returned
when striken accidently by the goalkeeper.
</P>
<P>
Two minutes later, Vijayan repeated the feat.
</P>
<P>
And two minutes before the match ended, an excellent pass into
space made Bhaichung Bhutia head a third goal for the Indians.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh tied the Maldives 1-1 on Friday.
</P>
<P>
India offers the best facilities, programs and academies for
its team in the region.
</P>
<P>
Nepal, India, Bhutan, Sri Lanka, Pakistan and the Maldives are
competing in the tournament, the biggest ever in the region.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka will play Nepal on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka defeated Pakistan 2-0 on Saturday. Pakistan beat
Nepal 2-0 at the opening match on Thursday. 
</P>
