<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Haier Seeks Larger Market Share Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, September 7 (Xinhua)-- One of China's best-known
electronic appliances supplier, Haier Group, based in thod coastal
city in Shandong Province, has become the largest Asian
exporter of air-conditioners for Europe.
</P>
<P>
Haier now has nearly 7,000 sales agents in Europe, and expanded
its market to 106 countries and regions, according to a report
from the Qingdao government.
</P>
<P>
Outlining an ambitious market strategy to raise the exports to
one third of its output, Haier has exerted great efforts on
technology upgrading and quality warranty. It has gotten quality
certificates from the United States, Canada, Germany and Japan,
among others.
</P>
<P>
The company's refrigerators, freezers and air-conditioners have
also had the globally-recognized ISO9001 certificate.
</P>
<P>
Growing out of the former Qingdao Refrigerator Factory, a small
state-owned firm, Haier now contributes one third of the city's
industrial profits, and produces a series of electronic appliances
including its flagship products -- refrigerators and air-conditioners.
</P>
<P>
By last June, Haier had generated 4.8 billion yuan (578 million
U.S. dollars) in retail sales, accounting for 13 percent of the
city's total. 
</P>
</TEXT>
