<HEADLINE> Color TV Sets Festival Opens In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The '97 Shanghai Color TV Sets
Festival opened today in Shanghai, China's largest industrial
city, giving domestic color TV manufacturers an opportunity to
show off their new products.
</P>
<P>
The event is sponsored by the State Information Center (SIC),
Shanghai's Municipal Commission of Commerce, and the country's
10 top color TV makers including Changhong and Konca.
</P>
<P>
The show has been held amid reports that domestic manufacturers
are competing favorably in a market war against foreign
companies.
</P>
<P>
According to SIC statistics, home-made products now make up 76
percent of retail sales and 63 percent of wholesales in the
domestic market, up 15 percent and 20 percent over the figures of
early 1996.
</P>
<P>
The statistics also show a remarkable increase in the sales of
locally-made large TV sets.
</P>
<P>
However, some local experts are worried about the present
situation of the country's color TV-making industry. Of China's
some 100 TV sets manufacturers, 80 percent has an annual output of
less than 500,000 sets each, while only five percent each produces
over one million sets a year.
</P>
<P>
And, there is a technological gap between home-made TV sets and
foreign ones, they say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
