<HEADLINE> Security Beefed Up in Lagos University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The police has cordoned off the
University of Lagos following violence between rival secret cult
members which claimed the lives of two students at the weekend.
</P>
<P>
Another round of secret cult clashes killed a final year
philosophy student and a part three mechanical engineering
student on Thursday and Saturday respectively, the New Nigerian
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The first one was shot dead while the other was killed during
a counter attack by one of the opposing cult groups, the official
newspaper said, quoted a students union leader.
</P>
<P>
A meeting of the students union, government officials and
university authorities decided on Saturday that security
operatives should be drafted into the campus to protect lives and
property.
</P>
<P>
As part of the measures to checkmate the activities of the
campus hoodlums, the parley also decided to seal up the rooms of
the cultists within the campus.
</P>
<P>
According to the newspaper, the case has been transferred to
the State Criminal Investigation Department for investigation,
but no person l has so far been arrested in connection with the
incidents.
</P>
<P>
Apart from increasing cases of armed robbery, secret cult
menace has constituted a source of worry to Nigerians as the
cultists have continued to unleash terror on the ivory towers
across the country, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Their nefarious activities have always led to a loss of lives
while in most occasions, academic activities have been paralyzed.
</P>
<P>
In a recent public outing, Chief of General Staff Lt. Gen.
Oladipo Diya said that stiffer penalties were being worked out
against campus cultists. 
</P>
