<HEADLINE> Arab Nations Praise China's Foreign Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Arab countries highly value
China's dedicated pursuit of an independent foreign policy of
peace which is based on the five principles of peaceful
co-existence and has achieved "tremendous success," said a top
Arab official.
</P>
<P>
In a recent written interview with Xinhua, Mohamed A. Saket,
head of the Mission of the League of Arab States, said China has
always taken a firm stand against hegemony and supports the just
causes of the third world countries.
</P>
<P>
China always joins other developing nations and all
peace-loving countries in "making positive contributions to
maintaining regional and world peace, promoting common development
and opposing hegemonism, power politics and unjust and
unreasonable behavior in the international community," he added.
</P>
<P>
Acknowledging that China is the sole developing country among
the five permanent members of the United Nations Security Council,
Saket said that "China has made important contributions to the UN
in safeguarding the rights and interests of developing countries
and solving regional disputes."
</P>
<P>
The UN needs China's involvement, and "China will best
understand the aspiration of developing countries in the UN and
international affairs in the coming years," he said, hoping that
China will contribute still more to the reform of the UN
organizational structure.
</P>
<P>
In a separate interview with Xinhua, Egyptian Ambassador to
China Helmy Bedeir said that as a permanent member of the UN
Security Council, China is in the unique position to "continue the
positive and constructive role it has always played" in economic
and social growth facing the developing countries.
</P>
<P>
Bedeir pointed out that China's role is much appreciated on a
global level regarding issues such as UN reform, disarmament and
fighting terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Saket also noted that China, as the biggest developing country,
needs a peaceful international environment for its domestic
construction and "China has made great efforts and scored
tremendous successes in establishing a peaceful international
environment."
</P>
<P>
Both men held that China's prosperity and development are
significant to Asia and the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
Saket said that Arab countries have a traditional friendship
with China, and they are "willing to develop bilateral and
multilateral cooperation based on equality and mutual benefit."
</P>
<P>
"We are convinced that China will continue to make unremitting
efforts with the Arab states for peace and stability in the Middle
East and the world as a whole and for safeguarding the interests
of the developing countries," Saket said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
