<HEADLINE> Optic Cable Network to Enrich TV, Radio Entertainment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- In a couple of years, a TV
viewers in the Chinese capital may order a program from the
Beijing Cable TV Station, which will be sent at the time the
viewer prefers and on a special channel with limited access.
</P>
<P>
This scenario will come true when the construction of a major
optic cable network is completed in the city, according to the
Beijing Cable Broadcast and TV Network Center.
</P>
<P>
The urban part of the optic cable network consists of a
round-city super trunk line, as well as grade-1 and grade-2 trunk
lines.
</P>
<P>
People living in Hepingli district in the city's northern part
will be the first able to watch TV programs from the network, as
construction of the the section around their area is to be
completed in two months, said the center.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the suburban part of the network will start
soon, it added.
</P>
<P>
Once it is fully operational, the network will be able to send
programs on 47 TV channels and 18 stereo FM channels
simultaneously.
</P>
<P>
"Then Beijing people can listen to hi-fi radio programs and
watch hi-definition TV shows," it said.
</P>
<P>
The network will also enable local residents to have access to
video phone, video conference, remote education, TV shopping, and
computer networking services, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
