<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Business Volume at Shanghai's Fund Center Plunges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 7 (xinhua) -- Turnover at the
Shanghai-based fund center dropped markedly in August while
business through intermediary services surged, the latest
statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Business volume in August was down 8.8 percent from July to
5.31 billion yuan, which was also 64 percent less than that for
the corresponding month of last year.
</P>
<P>
A breakdown shows that borrowings in August plunged 57.9
percent to 1.223 billion yuan, while lendings dived 58.3 percent
to 1.227 billion yuan. Outstanding borrowings and lendings reached
653 million yuan by the end of last month, down 82.2 percent from
July.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attribute the drastic decline in total business volume
to an improved interbank money market and increased risk awareness
of commercial banks.
</P>
<P>
Statistics also show that deals struck through intermediary
services reached 28.66 billion yuan, about 141.6 percent of the
total for the first seven months of this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
