<HEADLINE> Porcelain Show in East China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Jingdezhen, a city in east
China's Jiangxi Province, also reputed as the world's "porcelain
capital," is expected to hold a one-month activity in October
highlighting the Chinese art.
</P>
<P>
The event, part of the Visit China '97 tourism campaign,
includes a display of ancient porcelain and pottery ware unearthed
over the past 15 years, at which 13 first-grade rare pieces from
the Yuan (1271-1368), Ming (1368-1644) and Qing (1644-1911)
dynasties will be on view to the public for the first time.
</P>
<P>
Among the exhibits are 60 items representing the highest skills
in China's pottery and porcelain-making processes.
</P>
<P>
Visitors will also have opportunities to watch potters at work,
according to the sponsor. 
