<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanxi Works with International Groups for Pollution Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, September 7 (Xinhua) -- North China's Shanxi Province
has made great progress in controling environmental pollution by
cooperating with foreign companies in technology, equipment and
funds.
</P>
<P>
The province, one of China's major energy and heavy industrial
bases, has contributed greatly to the Chinese economy by
developing various chemical and industrial products over the past
decades.
</P>
<P>
However, its environment is getting worse, due to poor
equipment and backward technology.
</P>
<P>
Since 1994, the province has worked jointly with financial
organizations in Germany, the United States, France and Japan, to
clean its air and rivers.
</P>
<P>
The city of Yangquan used 4.9 million US dollars in loans from
France to start a wastewater control project. Once completed,
80,000 tons of wastewater will be handled each day, half of which
is expected to be recycled, reported the province.
</P>
<P>
A donation of 3.21 million US dollars from Norway is to be used
next year to set up centers for air and water purification,
provincial authorities said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
