<HEADLINE> Another Israeli Soldier Killed in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, September 7 (Xinhua) -- One Israeli soldier was
killed in this morning's fighting with Lebanese guerrillas in
south Lebanon, according to Lebanese security sources.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese Orient Radio quoted the sources as saying that the
Israeli soldier was killed when Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or
Party of God, launched an attack on a position of Israeli
troops in the western sector of the Israeli self-proclaimed
security zone in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli troops immediately retaliated the attack by
shelling Hezbollah's positions nearby. But the details of the
fighting have not been revealed by the sources, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
On Friday morning, some 11 Israeli soldiers were killed, four
others wounded and one was missing in a fighting with Lebanese
army and resistance fighters.
</P>
<P>
The death of the Israeli soldier in today's fighting raised
the number of Israeli death in this year to 31, in addition to 76
others wounded in their battles with Lebanese forces.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up the 15-mile-wide "security zone" in South Lebanon
in 1985 to prevent cross-border attacks by anti-Israeli Hezbollah
guerrillas who have been fighting to force Israel out of the
Lebanese territory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
