<HEADLINE> Pakistan Considers Blacklisting Cheating Exporters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Pakistani government is
considering a proposal to blacklist the exporters, who are
involved in cheating foreign buyers, in a bid to protect the
country's export credibility, sources close to the Commerce
Ministry said today.
</P>
<P>
The government has taken serious notice of complaints from
European, Far Eastern and American buyers against some Pakistani
exporters who have been involved in supplying sub-standard goods,
the sources said.
</P>
<P>
A blacklist of about 20 such exporters, who have been earning
illegally at the cost of the country's export credibility, has
already been prepared by the government, they said.
</P>
<P>
The government would also bring a law against cheating
exporters and there was possibility to blacklist them for at least
10 years, the sources said.  
