<HEADLINE> Large Berths to be Added to Coastal Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Twenty large shipping berths
are to be added in three major port cities of Fujian province in
the coming three years, significantly raising the handling
capacity.
</P>
<P>
Each of the new berths is capable of accommodating 10,000-ton
ships, and will bring the total handling capacity of Xiamen,
Quanzhou, and Zhangzhou to 50 million tons.
</P>
<P>
At present, the three cities have a combined 151 wharfs and
docks where there are 19 large berths for ships of over 10,000
deadweight tons.
</P>
<P>
In addition to dozens of domestic shipping routes from the three
cities, Quanzhou and Xiamen have opened links to the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region and Japan, and Xiamen has sent
regular container liners to Singapore, the United States, the
Republic of Korea and the Mediterranean countries. 
</P>
