<HEADLINE> August Foreign Exchange Turnover Down in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Foreign exchange turnover
declined at the Shanghai-based China Foreign Exchange Trade System
in August, while the Chinese currency strengthened slightly
against the US dollar.
</P>
<P>
The lastest official statistics show that a total of 5.97
billion US dollars in foreign exchange changed hands last month,
down 18.9 percent from July. The average daily transaction
declined by 15.2 percent to 284 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The total amount includes 5.58 billion US dollars, 2.52 billion
Hong Kong dollars, 6.868 billion Japanese yen. The three figures
were down 19.3, 14.2 and 13.2 percent, respectively, from July.
</P>
<P>
The trade-weighted value of the US dollar was quoted at 8.2884
yuan on the last trading day of August 29, down 19 points from a
month ago. The Hong Kong dollar was changed for 1.0792 yuan at the
end of August, up three points. The yen lost 804 points against
the yuan to end at 100 to 6.9341 on August 29. 
</P>
