<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Ban Dynamite Fishing in Lake Victoria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzanian
government plans to launch a move in Lake Victoria against
fishermen using "thiodan" (a dynamite and a pesticide against
pests destroying cotton).
</P>
<P>
"It's true that fishing using thiodan is rampant in Lake
Victoria and it's a threat to the people," said Zakia Meghji,
Minister for Natural Resources and Tourism, in an interview with
the local Sunday Observer paper.
</P>
<P>
Meghji said that although relevant authorities in the lake
zone regions of Mwanza, Kagera and Mara have taken measures to
contain the situation, the operation should be done to "get rid
of this malpractice which is a health hazard".
</P>
<P>
Recalling the recent operation which was done in Dar es
Salaam, Coast and Tanga coastal waters of the Indian Ocean, the
Minister said it is effective.
</P>
<P>
From July 1, an operation against thiodan fishing has been
launched in the above-said regions and it is jointly executed by
the Tanzania Police Force and the Tanzania People's Defense
forces. The operation will also be carried out in the southern
Tanzania regions of Mtwara and Lindi, according to Meghji.
</P>
</TEXT>
