<HEADLINE> China to Export More Machinery &AMP; Electronics in Second Half Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- China's machinery and
electronics exports are expected to grow steadily in the second
half of the year owing to a number of favourable factors such as
low exchange rate and accelerated efforts to pay back rebates.
</P>
<P>
The three-percent growth in the world economy this year, the highest in
the 1990s as predicted by the United Nations, will demand a lot of
machinery and electronics, thus providing a chance for Chinese
exporters to increase their performance in the world market,
"China Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
China's exports of machinery and electronics grew 25 percent in
the first six months of this year to 25.6 billion US
dollars. Imports dropped nine percent to 1.1 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Between January and June, general trade exports of machinery
and electronics rose 27.8 percent, compared to a 24.3 percent
growth in processing trade exports.
</P>
<P>
Of the three categories of machinery and electronics products,
electronics commodities led the other two with a volume of 9.7
billion US dollars, followed by machinery at 9.46 billion US
dollars, and light industry at 6.42 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Machinery exports grew fastest at 27.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, China's efforts to increase its export destinations
resulted in satisfying achievements. Exports to Latin America and
Africa developed at a rate of more than 30 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
