<HEADLINE> Stampede Kills 5 in Dhaka Garment Unit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- At least five female garment
workers were killed in a stampede Saturday night when they made a
frantic bid to escape after hearing a fire alarm in the Mohakhali
area of Bangladesh's capital Dhaka city, local press reported
today.
</P>
<P>
About 50 others, including two policemen, were also injured in
the incident and they were admitted to the hospitals adjacent to
the garment factories, said local police.
</P>
<P>
The fire broke out at Novelli garments on the fifth floor of
the seven-storey building in the Mohakhali area and quickly spread
to another factory, Modern Garments, on the same floor.
</P>
<P>
Fire fighters rushed to the spot and brought the flame under
control within half an hour. Fire Brigade in its preliminary
report said the fire had originated from the switch room of the
Novelli garments.
</P>
<P>
Soon after the incident, hundreds of people tried to enter the
factories to know the fate of their relatives hearing the rumor of
many deaths.
</P>
<P>
Police cordoned off the entire area, lobbed several teargas
canisters and resorted to baton charge to disperse the crowd.
</P>
<P>
This is the third tragic incident in garment factories within
two months in the same area.  
</P>
</TEXT>
