<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Navy Destroys Tamil Rebel Command Boat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 9 (Xinhua) -- A Tamil rebel command boat was
 completely destroyed and three other boats badly damaged by Sri
Lanka's navy Friday night in the Northern province, local press
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The reports said the navy patrol boat after observing a group
of rebel boats around 10:45 p.m. Friday moved fast towards
northwards of Challai and were fired at.
</P>
<P>
The rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) fired
rocket-propelled grenades and heavy weapons at the navy boats.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE command boat was completely destroyed and was sunk
while three other boats managed to escape.
</P>
<P>
One navy boat was slightly damaged and sailor received minor
injures in the fighting, the reports added.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been waging a guerrilla war for a separate
Tamil state in the north and east of the island country since
1983. 
