<HEADLINE> Economic News Briefs From Mercosur Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 6 (Xinhua) -- The following are recent
economic news briefs from Mercosur, the biggest commercial bloc in
South America grouping Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay,
with Chile and Bolivia as associate members:
</P>
<P>
LIMA -- The Andean Nations Community (CAN) will present
Mercosur with three lists of products for tariff elimination
within the talks for free trade in the region, said Peruvian Vice
Minister of Integration Diego Calmet.
</P>
<P>
The Andean Community comprises Bolivia, Colombia, Ecuador, Peru
and Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- A business delegation headed by Uruguayan Vice
President Hugo Batalla signed an agreement worth 43 million
U.S. dollar with Brazilian businessmen during a visit last week to
the Brazilian states of Minas Gerais and Para.
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- The Brazilian consumer prices index for the
last 12 months dropped to 4.6 percent, the lowest in the past 47
years.
</P>
<P>
The price index was issued by the Economic Research Institute
Foundation of Sao Paulo University.
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- Brazilian food exports to Argentina stood at
154.4 million U.S. dollars in 1996, down 25.5 percent from the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Trade Committee of the Brazilian Industry and
Commerce Ministry said Brazilian imports of Argentine products
rose by 10.5 percent to 244.7 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Argentine motor vehicle exports rose in August
to a historical record of 23,339 units, a 21.4 percent increase
over the previous month, and an increase of 111.4 percent over a
year ago.
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Argentina proposed to its Mercosur partners
that a telecommunications common market be created after the model
applied by the European Union, said Argentine Communications
Minister German Kamerth.
</P>
<P>
Argentina proposed a common tariff among the four members of
the bloc on telephone calls within Mercosur, Kamerth added.
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Some 300 specialists from the Mercosur countries
and Europe will attend a Mental Health Conference to be held here
on October 7 to draft a document for Mercosur, which will contain
the guidelines for regional policies and social actions with
regard to mental health care. 
</P>
</TEXT>
