<HEADLINE> Iberoamerica Seminar on Parliamentary Reform Ends in Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September 6 (Xinhua) -- The seminar on the
Iberoamerican parliamentary modernization and reform ended today
in Valparaiso, the seat of the Chilean Congress, with the adoption
of a charter for the modernization of Iberoamerican parliament.
</P>
<P>
The document said the target of the parliamentary reform in the
Iberoamerican countries is to give depth and permanence to their
commitments with the citizens, to their desires and interests and
strengthen the democratic system.
</P>
<P>
The document was signed by representatives of 20 Iberoamerican
countries and four representatives of regional parliaments.
</P>
<P>
The Iberoamerican countries which began their seminar Thursday
said that it was necessary to strengthen the legality of the
parliaments and to deepen the transparency and public character of
the discussion of their commissions.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of parliament from Chile, Argentina, Paraguay,
Venezuela, Costa Rica, Cuba, Spain and the president of Latin
American Parliament attended the seminar. 
</P>
