<HEADLINE> Indonesia's AIDS/HIV Victims Up by 20 in 1 Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The number of Indonesians
suffering from AIDS/HIV has increased by 20 from 558 in July to
578 in August, a Health Ministry official said.
</P>
<P>
Of the 578, 438 have tested HIV positive and 140 are suffering
from full-blown AIDS, Antara news agency today quoted Hadi M.
Abdinegoro, an official from the Health Ministry, as saying.
</P>
<P>
Hadi said here Saturday that most of the victims (some 478
people) were infected through homosexual or heterosexual
intercourse.
</P>
<P>
