<HEADLINE> Croatia Win World Cup Qualifier Against Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Captain Zvonimir Boban hit
the winner for Croatia in a 3-2 victory over Bosnia in a World Cup
European group One match at Zagreb on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The victory sustained Croatia's hopes of reaching the finals of
next year's World Cup in France. They are now third with 12
points, one point behind both Greece and second-placed Denmark.
</P>
<P>
Croatia went a goal behind in the 18th minute when defender
Robert Jarni scored an own goal with a back pass.
</P>
<P>
But they hit back strongly and levelled the scoring when
Everton's Slaven Bilic unleashed a 30-meter shot that beat
goal-keeper Mirsad Dedic in 27th minute.
</P>
<P>
Silvio Maric put the Croats 2-1 ahead from close range after a
free kick by Igor Cvitanovic in 40th minute.
</P>
<P>
Bosnia levelled in the 55th minute after another mistake by
Croat goal-keeper Ladic, whose failure to control a free kick
allowed striker Hasan Salihamidzic to score from a rebound.
</P>
<P>
Boban hit in the winner when he took a pass just inside the
area. He turned and fired a low shot into Deddic's left corner.
</P>
</TEXT>
