<HEADLINE> Ukraine Wants Luxembourg to Support its WTO Membership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian Prime Minister Valery
Pustovoitenko said today that he hopes Luxembourg will support
Ukraine in joining the World Trade Organization as soon as
possible.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with his Luxembourg counterpart Jean-Claude
Juncker, Pustovoitenko said his country also wishes to gain
support from Luxembourg, the European Union's rotating Presidency,
for Ukraine's integration with the EU.
</P>
<P>
He said Ukraine's foreign economic policy aims to strengthen
its integration with the world economy.
</P>
<P>
In a joint communique, the two governments said the close ties
and cooperation between Ukraine and the EU would promote Ukrainian
economic reform and the integration.
</P>
<P>
Juncker, who arrived here Friday to attend a Ukrainian-EU
meeting, said a strong and independent Ukraine constitutes a
decisive factor in promoting the security and stability of
Europe. 
</P>
