<HEADLINE> Finland Beat Switzerland 2-1 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GEVENA, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Finland upset hosts Switzerland
2-1 in a World Cup qualifier in Lausanne on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
STriker Jari Litmanen released a crisp left-foot shot in the
16th minute and Antti Sumiala added a superb individual goal at
the 79th mintue to give the Finland team a surprising 2-1 victory.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland hit a late goal from Adrian Kunz in the 90th minute
but missed an array of scoring chances. Finland's Glasgow
Rangers 'keeper Antii Niemi made several superb saves.
</P>
<P>
Finland are now second in the group behind leaders Norway who
had secured their place in next year's finals after beating
Azerbaijan 1-0 earlier on the day. Finland have never qualified
for the World Cup finals. 
