<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany Draw Portugal in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Germany had a narrow escape
from their second ever defeat in a World Cup qualifier as they got
the equalizer only nine minutes before the final whistle in a
group nine match against Portugal.
</P>
<P>
Portugal, who gave Germany their only loss so far on the way to
World Cup finals by beating them 1-0 in Stuttgart in 1985, nearly
did it again after opening the scoring through Pedro BArbosa in
the 71st minute.
</P>
<P>
But the Portuguese team lost their inspirational midfielder Rui
Costa who was sent off for a second bookable offence in the 76th
minute. The Germans took the chance and levelled the scoring
through substitute Ulf Kirsten in the 81st minute.
</P>
<P>
After the draw, the two teams both have 16 points, one point
behind group leader Ukraine. But Portugal have played one more
game than the German team.
</P>
<P>
Germany need to win their last two group matches to make sure
their qualification for the 1998 World Cup finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
