<HEADLINE> Overseas-Funded Enterprises Run Well In Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The performance of
overseas-funded enterprises in Zhuzhou, an important industrial
city in China's Hunan province, has been described as "very good"
in the first half of the year by local officials.
</P>
<P>
The 225 overseas-funded enterprises in Zhuzhou had total sales
of 1.6 billion yuan (nearly 200 million US dollars) during that
period, and foreign funds have helped a large number of state-owned
enterprises in the city regain their vitality.
</P>
<P>
The South Engine Company, a major producer of motorcycles and
other products now co-operating with business people from various
countries, is expected to increase its market share four-fold.
</P>
<P>
A number of large-scale specialized markets have also appeared
in Zhuzhou.
</P>
<P>
The "Zhuzhou Garment World" and the "Central and South China
Motorcycle Market", both among the biggest in the country, did
more than 250 million and 125 million US dollars in annual
business respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
