<HEADLINE> Costa Rican Exports Continue Increasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rican exports grew 14.8
percent during the first seven months of this year, compared to
the same period of 1996, the Foreign Trade Promotion (Procomer)
agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to Procomer data, sales abroad reached by July of
this year 2.425 billion U.S. dollars, against 2.113 billion
dollars in the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The United States acquired 49 percent of Costa Rican exports
while the European Union and the Central American countries bought
21 percent and 13 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
According to official estimates, exports will reach in 1997 4.8
billion dollars in total. 
</P>
