<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dutch Qualify for 1998 World Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 6 (Xinhua) -- The Netherlands joined
Romania and Norway as European qualifiers for next year's World
Cup finals when it defeated Belgium 3-1 on Saturday in Rotterdam.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch nationals almost duplicated their three-to-nothing
win from their away leg of the group seven qualifying tournament
which was held in Brussels last December.
</P>
<P>
Lorenzo de Staelens converted a 67th-minute penalty for a
face-saving lone goal in the game which saw the hosts dominate by
controlling the ball from start to end.
</P>
<P>
Controversial Dutch striker Patrick Kluivert proved his worth
of transfer to AC Milan, by scoring one goal and setting up
another.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-two minutes into play, defender Jaap Stam headed in a
corner kick from Wim Jonk to put the Dutch side on the scoreboard
first while Kluivert dribbled into the Belgian box after
receiving a pass from Denis Bergkamp only to make it 2-0 at the
54th minute.
</P>
<P>
Six minutes from the final whistle, Kluivert returned a clean
pass to advancing Bergkamp who duely scored with a left-footed
slot to seal the game away from the Belgians.
</P>
<P>
Kluivert, who moved to AC Milan from Ajax, has been under
intense media pressure and been criticized at home after last
year's conviction for causing death by dangerous driving,
followed by this year's rape charges that were later dropped.
</P>
<P>
He had said that he would quit the Dutch eleven if he should
be booed in Saturday's match with Belgium.
</P>
<P>
Danish referee Kim Milton Nielsen awarded the visiting sides
with a penalty kick after Jonk mowed down Luis Oliveira inside
the box.
</P>
<P>
The Belgians, who had hoped a miracle would send them to
France, have now to wait for more than a month before knowing for
sure whether they will join others in the cup finale.
</P>
<P>
A late goal by Georges Grun in another World Cup qualifier
against the Netherlands sent the Belgians into the 1986 cup
finals. That match was also played in Rotterdam.
</P>
<P>
Belgium next plays Wales on October 11 in Brussels and a win
would qualify the Red Demons into the play-off round.
</P>
<P>
The winners of the nine groups in the European qualifying
tourney go to France while the best runner-up will also qualify.
The remaining eight runners-up will then pair off and play a
home-and-away play-off in October and November to decide who will
be the last four of the 14 European qualifiers.
</P>
<P>
France is an automatic qualifier as the host to next year's
World Cup. 
</P>
</TEXT>
